None elevation curve

3D plot of bicycle infrastructure around Medborgarplatsen on Sdermalm.

Uses vector data of bicycle paths from Trafikverket which contains x,y,z linestrings.
Also uses height measurements in raster format from Lantmteriet.

Mapping is done with a compination of rasterio, gdal, matplotlib and geopandas.

import geopandas as gpd
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import shapely
import rasterio
import rasterio.plot

import warnings
warnings.simplefilter(action='ignore')  # mute geopanda warning when reading file

from osgeo import gdal
from shapely import ops

def get_XYZ(file):
    tif = gdal.Open(file)
    crs = rasterio.open(file).crs
    tifArray = tif.ReadAsArray()
    gt = tif.GetGeoTransform()

    px = gt[1]
    py = -gt[-1]

    xmin = gt[0]
    ymax = gt[3]

    width = px*tif.RasterXSize
    height = py*tif.RasterYSize

    xx = np.linspace(xmin, xmin+width, int(width/px), endpoint=True)
    yy = np.linspace(ymax - height, ymax, int(height/py), endpoint=True)

    X, Y = np.meshgrid(xx, yy)    
    Z = tif.GetRasterBand(1).ReadAsArray()
    return X, Y, Z

X, Y, Z = get_XYZ("data/merged.tif")

# Merging all multilinestrings into linestrings
gdf.geometry = gdf.geometry.apply(lambda x: ops.linemerge(x) if isinstance(gdf.geometry.values[0], shapely.geometry.multilinestring.MultiLineString) else x)

# Retrieve x, y, z coordinates from geometries -- quite verbose
gdf["x"] = gdf.geometry.apply(lambda geoms:np.array([coords[0] for coords in geoms.coords]))
gdf["y"] = gdf.geometry.apply(lambda geoms:np.array([coords[1] for coords in geoms.coords]))
gdf["z"] = gdf.geometry.apply(lambda geoms:np.array([coords[2] for coords in geoms.coords]))
xs = gdf.x.values
ys = gdf.y.values
zs = gdf.z.values

ax = plt.figure(figsize = (20, 20)).add_subplot(projection="3d")
fig = ax.get_figure()
ax.plot_surface(X, Y[::-1], Z, cmap=plt.cm.Greys, alpha=0.4)
for x, y, z in zip(xs, ys, zs): 
    z[z < -100] = np.nan
    z = pd.DataFrame(z).interpolate().values.ravel()
    ax.plot(x, y, z, 'r')

from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import axes3d
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from IPython.display import HTML
import matplotlib.animation as animation

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (20, 20))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

ax.set_axis_off()

def init():
    ax.plot_surface(X, Y[::-1], Z, cmap=plt.cm.Greys, alpha=0.3)
    for x, y, z in zip(xs, ys, zs): 
        z[z < -100] = np.nan
        z = pd.DataFrame(z).interpolate().values.ravel()
        ax.plot(x, y, z+1, 'r')
    return fig,

def animate(i):
    ax.view_init(elev=30., azim=3.6*i)
    return fig,

ani = animation.FuncAnimation(fig, animate, init_func=init,
                               frames=100, interval=100, blit=True)    

plt.close('all')

ani.save("mygif.gif")
